1(1)+\frac12\left(\frac12\right)+\frac14\left(\frac14\right)+\cdots+\frac{1}{2^n}\left(\frac{1}{2^n}\right)+\cdots=\frac{1}{1-\frac14}=\boxed{\dfrac 43}.
A_n = (\frac{1}{2^n},\frac{1}{2^{n-1}} ]
\lambda
   f = \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{2^n}I_{A_n}. 
   \int_0^1 f(x) dx = \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{2^n} \lambda(A_n) = \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{2^n} \left(\frac{1}{2^{n-1}} - \frac{1}{2^n} \right) = \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{2^n} \frac{1}{2^n} < \infty. 
